<Defs>

  <ThingDef Name="NCLMechDinergate" ParentName="BaseMechanoidWalker">
    <defName>NCL_Mech_Dinergate</defName>
    <label>Dinergate</label>
<description>Unit Archive: NCL-00 "Dinergate"
Origin: "Iron Law" Mass-Production Series

As NCL's first autonomous design, the Dinergate marked the transition from scrap-based to purpose-built mechanoids. This compact combat platform served diverse frontline roles across countless operations.

Its core chassis features a honeycomb bionic structure with living-metal joints, balancing durability and mass-production efficiency. 

Standard armament includes mid-range electro-lances and polymorphic manipulators that transition seamlessly between combat and utility roles. A rear-mounted drone deployment system provides tactical flexibility.

Though technically obsolete, Dinergate variants persist in stellar ruins - minimalist shells executing forgotten commands with lethal precision.</description>
    <statBases>
      <MarketValue>800</MarketValue>
      <MoveSpeed>6.0</MoveSpeed>
      <ArmorRating_Blunt>0.60</ArmorRating_Blunt>
	  <EMPResistance>0.20</EMPResistance>
      <ArmorRating_Sharp>0.60</ArmorRating_Sharp>
      <ShootingAccuracyPawn>3</ShootingAccuracyPawn>
      <PsychicSensitivity>0</PsychicSensitivity>
